frameDefinitions: An Agent manipulates a Sound_maker or a Cause causes the Sound_maker to emit a sound.
In this frame a Deformer deforms a Patient possibly against a Resistant_surface such that it undergoes a shape-change from its canonical or original shape into the Configuration, a new shape.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
An Agent changes a Part of a complex entity with regard to some Feature in order to achieve some Imposed_purpose affected by the Feature.
An Agent or Cause makes a Patient sharper or duller.
An Agent adjusts an Instrument to enable it to interact directly with a difficult-to-access Target_location.
frameExamples: The monks would <t>ring</t> the bell until sundown.
Ellen <t>crumpled</t> the paper into a ball.
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
I need to <t>adjust</t> the thermostat to around 80 degrees when she visits.
John is in the basement <t>sharpening</t> his axe.
If you <t>aim</t> your weapons somewhere else , I 'll be more likely to talk .
listRoleDefinitions: The individual that manipulates a Sound_maker so that it makes Noise.
The entity that produces the Noise, as a result of the action of the Agent.
The inanimate force of nature that causes the <fen>Sound_maker</fen> to produce noise.
The time at which the noise is produced.
The location at which the sound is produced.
The <fen>Deformer</fen> is the one who does the reshaping.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is an animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces an effect. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
A state that holds of the <fen>Patient</fen> or a relation that holds among the constituent parts of the <fen>Patient</fen> as a result of the arranging action.
The role <fen>Time</fen> identifies when the <fen>Deformer</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the <fen>Deformer</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
The individual that controls the value of a <fen>Feature</fen>.
The part of the complex entity which is changed in the process of adjusting.
The <fen>Feature</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Part</fen> is adjusted.
The time at which the adjusting occurs.
The location where the adjusting takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become more or less sharp.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is sharpened.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of sharpness.  Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> sharpens <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> sharpens the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The individual that manipulates the <fen>Instrument</fen> to enable interaction with the <fen>Targeted</fen>.
The <fen>Targeted</fen> is the entity located in an indirectly accessible location relative to the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The object manipulated by the <fen>Agent</fen> in order to interact with the <fen>Targeted</fen>.
The location that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to ready the <fen>Instrument</fen> to access.
The <fen>Activity</fen> is undertaken by the <fen>Agent</fen> and is directed towards the <fen>Targeted</fen> or <fen>Target_location</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> takes aim.
The place where the <fen>Agent</fen> aims at the <fen>Targeted</fen>.

<fex>The strong winds</fex> deformed the structure of the outhouse.
The lieutenant crushed it angrily with his boot <fex>before looking back at Hencke</fex>.

She adjusted <fex>the injectors</fex> to make the mixture leaner.
She adjusted <fex>the temperature of the oven</fex> so that the pie crust would brown a little.
<fex>The smith</fex> sharpened many knives in the days before the war.
Several cuts into the log had dulled <fex>the blade</fex>.
<fex>The relentless impacts against the wood</fex> gradually blunted the edge of this axe.
I tried to target <fex>his left thigh</fex> .
